Remember, intercostal nerves are continuations of ventral rami; they unite with dorsal rami to form spinal nerves in the intervertebral foramina.  
The intercostal nerves contain:
somatic motor axons which innervate skeletal muscle, 
sensory axons which monitor receptors throughout the thickness of the thoracic wall, from the skin to the parietal pleura
sympathetic postganglionic fibres that innervate vascular smooth muscle throughout the thickness of the body wall, and the arrector pili muscle and glands of the skin.
